<p><strong>Francis Bacon</strong>: “one has an intention, but what really happens comes about in working … In working, you are following this cloud of sensation in yourself, but don’t know what it really is.” That is, his work starts with an initial intention, but it quickly gives way to surprise and discovery. He operates on the high-level goal of making paintings, but the specific intentions of those paintings are not fixed in advance.</p>

